The paper deals with graph algorithms and specifically focuses on prime factorization of graphs. This falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Graph Theory (cs.GT). The algorithm presented in the paper is a local approach, which involves dividing the graph into patches and deriving global factors from them. This approach is commonly used in Computational Geometry (cs.CG) and Spatial Information (cs.SI) domains. Additionally, the paper deals with the practical application of graph prime factorization algorithms, which could also fall under the category of Data Structures (cs.DS).
